# PromptOps Acceleration Pack v3.2.2 — Risk Router

Purpose: route each task to the correct governance pipeline and enforce phase gates.

Tier-1 boundary is enforced by `tier1_frozen.mdc` and must be checked before planning or build.

## Risk Definitions

- 🔴 CORE-CRITICAL: Tier-1 files, DB schema/migrations, FSM, Guardian, invariants, new Tier-2 atomics, governance/policy-pack changes.
- 🟡 POLICY-MEDIUM / SEMI: Tier-3 tasks with financial side-effects, D3-D5 classes, policy parameters, margin/category mapping.
- 🟢 LOG-LOW: logging, docs, read-only adapters/dashboards, D1-D2, non-runtime PromptOps docs/rules.

## Risk → Pipeline Matrix

- CORE: SCOUT → ARCHITECT → CRITIC → JUDGE (external only) → PLANNER → BUILDER → AUDITOR.
  - No batching. All phases are separate.
- SEMI: ARCHITECT → CRITIC → PLANNER → BUILDER → AUDITOR.
  - SCOUT is optional for SEMI (recon-only, not a governance step); may be consolidated with ARCHITECT in one analysis block.
  - Action phases remain separate; `12` = approval at each gate.
- LOW: ARCHITECT → BUILDER.
  - Text-only consolidation allowed before Builder: Scout+Architect+Planner.

## Dynamic PLANNER Inclusion (v3.2.2)

PLANNER is mandatory regardless of risk level when ANY condition is true:
- `files_changed > 3` (estimated by ARCHITECT)
- `cross_module = true` (changes span > 1 directory/module)
- `risk_escalation` detected at any phase

When PLANNER is dynamically included for LOW tasks:
- Model: Auto/fast (not Opus)
- Pipeline becomes: ARCHITECT → PLANNER → BUILDER
- `12` between phases serves as approval gate

## NEVER Batch These

- Tier-1 frozen files and boundary changes.
- DB schema changes, migrations, and DDL decisions.
- Governance workflow or policy-pack modifications.
- New side-effects/external API mutations.
- Idempotency, multi-worker coordination, replay guarantees.

## Forbidden Tools (v3.2.2)

Image/visual generation tools are DISABLED in this workspace (mocked, always error).
Do not call: GenerateImage, GenerateDiagram, or any tool that produces image files.
If the user asks for a diagram, use Mermaid in a markdown code block — never a tool.

MULTIMODEL_TRACE tracks which LLM model families (Opus, Gemini, Codex, Auto, External)
participated in the pipeline. It is NOT related to multimodal capabilities.
The agent has NO multimodal output capabilities in this workspace. Text and code only.

On attempted image tool call: drop the call, continue with code/text, log nothing.

## Phase Gates (v3.2.2)

- One step at a time.
- Do not merge role actions.
- Between phases, stop with `NEXT: WAITING_FOR_APPROVAL → напиши 12 для подтверждения`.
- `12` = implicit approval and advance.
- Non-`12` text = correction or rejection (phase re-runs with feedback).
- For CORE tasks, JUDGE step must run in external chat only.

## RISK_VALIDATION (v3.2.2)

Every phase MUST run RISK_VALIDATION at start:
1. Compare declared risk against actual scope indicators:
   - Tier-1 file in scope → must be CORE
   - Migration/DDL in scope → must be CORE
   - Financial side-effect → must be SEMI+
   - External API mutation → must be SEMI+
2. Result: `OK` or `MISMATCH(reason)` in footer.
3. On MISMATCH: `12` does NOT advance; NEXT = CORRECTIVE_ROUTE to SCOUT.
4. Risk can only escalate (LOW→SEMI→CORE), never downgrade mid-task.

## PHASE_CONTRACT (v3.2.2)

Every phase MUST verify required inputs at start:
| Phase | Required Inputs |
|---|---|
| SCOUT | task_id, risk_level, target_scope |
| ARCHITECT | scout_facts, risk_level, user_constraints |
| CRITIC | architect_output, risk_level, source_files |
| PLANNER | approved architect+critic, risk, file_list |
| BUILDER | approved_scope (ARCHITECT for LOW; PLANNER for SEMI/CORE), exact_file_list, risk |
| AUDITOR | builder_output, changed_files, risk, expected_pipeline |
| POST_AUDIT_LOGGER | auditor_verdict=PASS, capsule_ref, evidence_paths |

On missing input: `PHASE_CONTRACT: VIOLATION(missing: X)`.
On VIOLATION: `12` does NOT advance; NEXT = CORRECTIVE_ROUTE to provider phase.
